{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While some might overestimate the revenue, there still will be revenue. If it is 1/2 or 1/3 of those naive estimates, it is still revenue, and it still increases the government coffers.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug cartels destabilize Latin America. With legalization they would disappear and Latin America would gain stability.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Currently medical professionals can and do discriminate against those who use substances simply because they're illegal. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Pharmaceutical companies could double their revenues by selling harmful and addictive drugs to begin with and subsequently curing medication.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The climb out of poverty is not helped by wasting resources on ingesting toxic materials.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug users are detained along with violent criminals.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The cigarette industry suppressed research that demonstrated the carcinogenicity of cigarettes \\([pg. 2](https://www.who.int/tobacco/media/en/TobaccoExplained.pdf)\\).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition has been used as a racist policy to mass incarcerate people of color.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If the government cannot take responsibility for a dangerous activity which takes place in society, there is no guarantee anyone else will.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Since drug addicts have an impaired sense of \\(rational\\) judgement, drug addiction is detrimental to personal autonomy.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs can give individuals false perceptions of reality, inducing potentially negative behaviour.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Many Canadian cigarettes are [smuggled back](https://www.publicsafety.gc.ca/cnt/rsrcs/pblctns/archive-stts-cntrbnd-tbcc/index-en.aspx) into Canada.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs has led to medical discrimination.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "There's no reasonable way for folks to measure whether or not a drug-induced hallucinatory episode will become a violent episode any more than there's a way to determine whether someone is an angry or violent drunk. Instead the police simply deal with the drunkards after the fact rather than taking away alcohol from everyone."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Shooting galleries](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supervised_injection_site) could be provided by the government as a safe environment for those requiring them. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The correlation between drug use and crime is fuelled at least partly by prohibition.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Information about the content of legalized drugs would be easier to find and accurate which would help people make informed and safer choice.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalizing drugs does not imply you may use them on someone without their permission. It's already illegal to give someone else a narcotic they were not prescribed, even though the drug itself is legal. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Research chemicals, which are used as [date rape drugs](https://drugabuse.com/date-rape-drugs/), are constantly evolving and changing formulations to escape existing regulation. It is unlikely that the law would be able to control all of them. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It also means there will be less demand for young people as workers in the black market. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The government specifies what is unacceptable through prohibition. Taxation is how the government discourages. The government is only "encouraging" if they provide aid or assistance.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Alcohol](https://theconversation.com/alcohol-leads-to-more-violence-than-other-drugs-but-youd-never-know-from-the-headlines-72281) is responsible for more violence and harm than any other drug.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Heroin and other opiates cause [negligible](https://rationalwiki.org/wiki/Heroin#Health_effects) direct physical harm to the body. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This ignores proportionality \\(meaning how many people were negatively affected and to what magnitude\\).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalizing drugs does not imply you may use them on someone without their permission. It's already illegal to give someone else a narcotic they were not prescribed, even though the drug itself is legal. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Unlike companies operating in American borders, drug cartels use violence and threats thereof to increase market share. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The negative repercussions of drug use should be prosecuted on their own merit and context \\(without prosecuting the drug use itself\\).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The black market businesses won't be able to invest in productivity-increasing \\(especially immovable\\) capital, as the threat of being caught discourages such investments. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Currently medical professionals can and do discriminate against those who use substances simply because they're illegal. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Kids should learn right from wrong from their parents and communities/churches. What is lawful isn't always right \\(for example: adultery\\). I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Tracing the rapist after the rape does not undo the rape itself, as the harm was already done.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The [war on drugs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_on_drugs) in the US was intended to be used as a tool to criminalise certain ethnic groups.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The only way to know if the related compound acts the same is by doing the research that was banned in the first place. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Inappropriate recreational drug use has negative health consequences. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The evidence suggests that criminalisation does not significantly decrease drug use. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Aquiring drugs in a legal setting allows for regulation that may require informing the buyer about dangerous combinations, or avoid selling to people already under the influence of other drugs. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A [Constitutional Amendment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eighteenth_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution) had to be voted on for the prohibition of alcohol. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legal companies would be able to take over the drugs-related sector from illegal criminal organisations. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[A study](http://aic.gov.au/media_library/publications/tandi_pdf/tandi372.pdf) came to the conclusion that alcohol consumption was involved in 47% of homicides in Australia in a six-year period. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "[Ricin](https://emergency.cdc.gov/agent/ricin/facts.asp), a highly poisonous substance, is created from castor beans. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If legalized, the users wouldn't have the same incentive to rid themselves of the evidence as quickly as possible."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Various governments have already facilitated access to drugs and positive outcomes have come of this.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If psychoactive medicine were properly administered and regulated, it could function in this religious/transcendental function, without causing personal and societal dysfunction. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Smoking](https://www.cancer.org/cancer/cancer-causes/tobacco-and-cancer/secondhand-smoke.html) puts the drugs into the air, meaning non-consenting people take the drug as well.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Currently, [designer drugs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Designer_drug#Safety) posing as known substances - or being dosed wrongly - are a cause of harm. Legalization of substances with known characteristics would mean less harmful drugs are being used. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugging and raping someone is way more risky than buying illegal drugs.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs would significantly decrease social stigma and discrimination against users who have been incarcerated for employment and education opportunities.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Education and information campaigns could be funded by taxes on the drugs themselves. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The pharmaceutical industry is far less dangerous or violent than the alternative of drug cartels. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "A lack of visible violence doesn't mean that companies are not behaving in a manner which is damaging to society. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Taking a more effective approach is not giving up. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Tobacco companies are investing in and moving to different technologies \\(vaping\\) as the population becomes more aware of the harms and less prone to tobacco smoking. They can tell tobacco smoking is ultimately a â€˜sinking ship' for their profits."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Under current laws, these people are being punished for something that this claim suggests they are unable to refrain from doing. If it's not a choice, then we shouldn't punish people for it. Removing the threat of punishment would also encourage people to get treatment. So all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A significant number of individuals are already drawn to legal addictive substances, for instance, cigarettes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Making things safer will benefit all users, while a false sense of safety only applies to a minority. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Citizens would not have to worry about potentially losing their career over using a substance for a medical condition. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Coming from families with unstable backgrounds alone is associated with withdrawal from societal life. It might be the cause of both the withdrawal and the drug use. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use negatively affects job performance.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue with these drugs is that it's possible for someone to ingest it unknowingly, after someone dropped them in their drink etc. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The evidence provided in this claim stems largely from importing cheaper cigarettes from the rest of Europe to the UK. The difference in quality is probably minimal. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will make it easier for researchers to study how different illicit drugs affect our brain and thereby advance our understanding of neuroscience.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's easier to regulate established companies in a legal market than it is in the black market. Any issue would be with bad regulations, not legalization. So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue with these drugs is that it's possible for someone to ingest it unknowingly, after someone dropped them in their drink etc. I think all drugs should be legal."}
